# Gate A Tester Onboarding (Single Page)

Goal: prove the core money path works end-to-end:
`install -> add one skill -> set engram -> verify generated config`.

Target time: **15 minutes max**.  
If you are blocked for more than 3 minutes on any step, stop and report.

## 0) Prerequisites (1 minute)

- Node.js 20+
- pnpm 9+
- PowerShell or terminal

From repo root:

```powershell
pnpm install
pnpm build
```

## 1) Start fresh local state (1 minute)

Create a minimal OpenClaw base config:

```powershell
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force "$HOME\\.openclaw" | Out-Null
'{"skills":{"entries":{}}}' | Set-Content "$HOME\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json" -Encoding Ascii
```

Initialize LobeSter:

```powershell
pnpm lobe -- init
pnpm lobe -- start
```

Leave the server terminal running.

## 2) Add one skill (3 minutes)

Open a second terminal. Create a sample skill folder:

```powershell
$skillPath = "$env:TEMP\\lobester-sample-skill"
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force $skillPath | Out-Null
@"
{
  "name": "Sample Skill",
  "openclawKey": "sample_skill",
  "version": "0.1.0"
}
"@ | Set-Content "$skillPath\\lobester.json" -Encoding Ascii
```

Install it through local API:

```powershell
$install = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:3210/api/skills/install" -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body (@{source=@{kind="local";ref=$skillPath}} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5)
$install.skill.id
```

Copy the printed `skill.id`.

## 3) Create engram and set (3 minutes)

```powershell
$engram = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:3210/api/presets" -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body (@{name="gate-a";skillIds=@($install.skill.id)} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5)
$apply = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://127.0.0.1:3210/api/openclaw/applyPreset" -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body (@{presetRef=$engram.preset.id} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5)
$apply.generatedConfigPath
```

## 4) Verify config output (2 minutes)

```powershell
Test-Path $apply.generatedConfigPath
Get-Content $apply.generatedConfigPath | Select-Object -First 20
```

Success criteria:

- `Test-Path` returns `True`
- Generated config includes your installed skill entry (`sample_skill`)
- No blocking error from `/api/openclaw/applyPreset`

## 5) Report back (2 minutes)

Send this exact summary:

- Total time (minutes)
- First blocker (if any)
- Did apply succeed? (`yes/no`)
- Generated config path
- 1 confusing step

---

## Time Check (author run)

I ran this flow in a fresh temp state from repo root (including `pnpm install` + `pnpm build`) and measured:

- **33.01 seconds** scripted end-to-end
- **0.55 minutes**

Human/manual execution should still be comfortably below the 15-minute gate.



